lisa-design:
- Assignee identifiers follow the BCH-1333 API contract exactly: a USER grant sends assigneeId = user.email; a GROUP grant sends assigneeId = group.name. The API normalizes (lower-case/trim) server-side, so the UI sends the raw email/name. Do NOT send user.id for user grants — the PDP keys roles by email.
- Delete targets the grant's id: user effective-role rows carry it as `assignmentId`, group rows as `id` (CCFRoleAssignment.id). Both DELETE /api/admin/role-assignments/:id.
- MANIFEST_ROLES is hardcoded in src/constants/permissions.ts (admin/viewer/auditor/contributor/agent) because the API exposes NO "list assignable roles" endpoint. This mirrors how permissions.ts already mirrors the manifest. The server still validates roleName against the manifest (400 on unknown), so this list is only picker convenience — keep it in sync with internal/authz/manifest.yaml.
- Permission gating uses PermissionGate (hide mode) for the Assign button and Remove buttons, per the BCH-1335 DoD ("assign/remove controls hidden without ROLE_ASSIGNMENT create/delete"). This intentionally differs from WorkflowInstanceRolesView's visible-but-disabled+tooltip approach.
- Removability rules: only a DIRECT + source=manual grant is removable. Inherited grants are read-only in the user view (manage them on the granting group). source=config grants are never removable (API returns 409; reconcile owns them, BCH-1334).
- The assign picker excludes roles the subject already holds DIRECTLY (avoids a guaranteed 409). A role held only via group inheritance stays directly assignable (a distinct, stronger grant), matching the API's separate user/group rows.
- GET role lists via useDataApi; POST/DELETE via useAuthenticatedInstance (matches GroupMembersPanel). Both panels refetch after a mutation so inherited/source flags stay correct rather than patching local state.
